# Remoting In:

Using NoMachine

### Installation/Setup:

Download From the link: https://download.nomachine.com/download/?id=1&platform=linux

Navigate to the directory and execute the command:

```sudo dpkg -i nomachine_9.3.7_1_amd64.deb```

#### Headless Fix (No monitor)
Without a monitor attatched, PC will stop generating display. Even an unpowered monitor will allow it to function though, but this is far too bulky for our purposes.

NoMachine will create a virtual display if it detects no display, but by default there is still a very limited display so need to run these commands.

```
sudo systemctl disable display-manager
sudo /etc/NX/nxserver --restart
```

The first command turns off the display for any physical monitor, and the second restarts the NoMachine server


**IMPORTANT:** You need to re-enable the display if we want to use a monitor again using the following command

```
sudo systemctl enable --now display-manager
```

### Connecting to IBEX PC

Make sure you are connected to the IBEX router.

Open NoMachine, and **volta** should be an option. If not or if that causes an error, then you can click **add** in the top left and use the static assigned IP address **192.168.0.10**.


